IX. PROSODY.

51. The earliest remains of Roman literature are, as we have seen, composed in the Saturnian metre, which proba· bly rests upon an accentual basis. This native metra was found to bc too rude and monotonous for dramatic verse; hence even the earliest writers in this sphere abandoned it for the quantitative measures used in their Greek originale.
